{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775890174833,"sessionID":"ses_284b2cd23ffexShxwd92QPDtT1","part":{"id":"prt_d7b4d8b29001yQ9cWqOJPWGbdG","messageID":"msg_d7b4d5dd3001bOjiFbbK3IYzXY","sessionID":"ses_284b2cd23ffexShxwd92QPDtT1","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-8e70966b2d284919ad51f8b821f0e1a9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-031/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-031/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-031 — RBAC 配置 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-031 — RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) |\n8: | Module | `manifests` |\n9: | Language | YAML |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: Define Kubernetes RBAC resources (ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding) for AgentCube components to enable secure, least-privilege access to Kubernetes API resources. Router uses namespace-scoped Role for Secret management; WorkloadManager uses cluster-wide ClusterRole for sandbox lifecycle management and CRD operations.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Architecture\n18: \n19: ### High-Level Architecture\n20: \n21: ```\n22: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n23: │                         RBAC Architecture                                    │\n24: │                     AgentCube Components                                     │\n25: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n26: │                                                                              │\n27: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n28: │  │                    Router RBAC (Namespace-scoped)                     │   │\n29: │  ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤   │\n30: │  │                                                                       │   │\n31: │  │   ┌─────────────────┐      ┌─────────────────┐                      │   │\n32: │  │   │ ServiceAccount  │──────│ RoleBinding     │                      │   │\n33: │  │   │ (namespace)     │      │ (namespace)     │                      │   │\n34: │  │   └─────────────────┘      └─────────────────┘                      │   │\n35: │  │                                  │                                   │   │\n36: │  │                                  ▼                                   │   │\n37: │  │                          ┌─────────────────┐                        │   │\n38: │  │                          │ Role            │                        │   │\n39: │  │                          │ (secrets only)  │                        │   │\n40: │  │                          └─────────────────┘                        │   │\n41: │  │                                                                       │   │\n42: │  │   Scope: {{ .Release.Namespace }}                                     │   │\n43: │  │   Permissions: secrets (get/list/watch/create/update/patch/delete)   │   │\n44: │  │   Conditional: router.rbac.create=true                                │   │\n45: │  │                                                                       │   │\n46: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n47: │                                                                              │\n48: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n49: │  │              WorkloadManager RBAC (Cluster-wide)                      │   │\n50: │  ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤   │\n51: │  │                                                                       │   │\n52: │  │   ┌─────────────────┐      ┌─────────────────────┐                  │   │\n53: │  │   │ ServiceAccount  │──────│ ClusterRoleBinding  │                  │   │\n54: │  │   │ (namespace)     │      │ (cluster-wide)      │                  │   │\n55: │  │   └─────────────────┘      └─────────────────────┘                  │   │\n56: │  │                                  │                                   │   │\n57: │  │                                  ▼                                   │   │\n58: │  │                          ┌─────────────────────┐                    │   │\n59: │  │                          │ ClusterRole         │                    │   │\n60: │  │                          │ (CRDs, Pods,        │                    │   │\n61: │  │                          │  Secrets,           │                    │   │\n62: │  │                          │  TokenReviews)      │                    │   │\n63: │  │                          └─────────────────────┘                    │   │\n64: │  │                                                                       │   │\n65: │  │   Scope: Cluster-wide                                                 │   │\n66: │  │   Permissions:                                                        │   │\n67: │  │     - agents.x-k8s.io: sandboxes                                      │   │\n68: │  │     - extensions.agents.x-k8s.io: sandboxclaims, templates, warmpools │   │\n69: │  │     - runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh: codeinterpreters, agentruntimes   │   │\n70: │  │     - core: pods, secrets                                             │   │\n71: │  │     - authentication.k8s.io: tokenreviews                             │   │\n72: │  │                                                                       │   │\n73: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n74: │                                                                              │\n75: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n76: ```\n77: \n78: ### RBAC Permission Model\n79: \n80: ```\n81: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n82: │                      Permission Flow Diagram                                  │\n83: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n84: │                                                                              │\n85: │   User/External ──────▶ Router ──────▶ Secrets (namespace-scoped)           │\n86: │         │                  │                                                │\n87: │         │                  │         ┌──────────────────────────────────┐   │\n88: │         │                  │         │ Role: secrets                    │   │\n89: │         │                  │         │ Verbs: get,list,watch,           │   │\n90: │         │                  │         │        create,update,patch,delete│   │\n91: │         │                  │         └──────────────────────────────────┘   │\n92: │         │                  │                                                │\n93: │         ▼                  ▼                                                │\n94: │                                                                              │\n95: │   Router ──────▶ WorkloadManager ──────▶ Kubernetes API                    │\n96: │         │                  │                                                │\n97: │         │                  │         ┌──────────────────────────────────┐   │\n98: │         │                  │         │ ClusterRole:                     │   │\n99: │         │                  │         │ - Sandboxes (full CRUD)          │   │\n100: │         │                  │         │ - CodeInterpreters (full CRUD)   │   │\n101: │         │                  │         │ - AgentRuntimes (read + status)  │   │\n102: │         │                  │         │ - Pods (read-only)               │   │\n103: │         │                  │         │ - Secrets (full CRUD)            │   │\n104: │         │                  │         │ - TokenReviews (create)          │   │\n105: │         │                  │         └──────────────────────────────────┘   │\n106: │         │                  │                                                │\n107: │         │                  ▼                                                │\n108: │         │         ┌─────────────────┐                                      │\n109: │         │         │ Sandbox CRDs    │──▶ Agent Sandbox Controller         │\n110: │         │         └─────────────────┘                                      │\n111: │         │         ┌─────────────────┐                                      │\n112: │         │         │ AgentCube CRDs  │──▶ WorkloadManager Reconciler        │\n113: │         │         └─────────────────┘                                      │\n114: │         │         ┌─────────────────┐                                      │\n115: │         │         │ Pods/Secrets    │──▶ Kubernetes Core API               │\n116: │         │         └─────────────────┘                                      │\n117: │         │                                                                  │\n118: │                                                                              │\n119: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n120: ```\n121: \n122: ### Component Relationships\n123: \n124: | Component | Scope | Resources | Purpose |\n125: |-----------|-------|-----------|---------|\n126: | Router ServiceAccount | Namespace | Pod identity | JWT signing key, identity secret access |\n127: | Router Role | Namespace | secrets | Manage session secrets |\n128: | Router RoleBinding | Namespace | SA → Role | Bind Router SA to Role |\n129: | WorkloadManager ServiceAccount | Namespace | Pod identity | CRD operations, sandbox lifecycle |\n130: | WorkloadManager ClusterRole | Cluster | CRDs, pods, secrets, tokenreviews | Full sandbox/interpreter management |\n131: | WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding | Cluster | SA → ClusterRole | Bind WM SA to ClusterRole |\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: ## Data Structures\n136: \n137: ### Router RBAC Schema\n138: \n139: #### ServiceAccount\n140: \n141: ```yaml\n142: apiVersion: v1\n143: kind: ServiceAccount\n144: metadata:\n145:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n146:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n147:   labels:\n148:     app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube\n149:     app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}\n150:     app.kubernetes.io/version: {{ .Chart.AppVersion }}\n151:     app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: {{ .Release.Service }}\n152: ```\n153: \n154: #### Role\n155: \n156: ```yaml\n157: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n158: kind: Role\n159: metadata:\n160:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n161:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n162:   labels:\n163:     app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube\n164:     app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}\n165: rules:\n166:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n167:     resources: [\"secrets\"]\n168:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n169: ```\n170: \n171: #### RoleBinding\n172: \n173: ```yaml\n174: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n175: kind: RoleBinding\n176: metadata:\n177:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n178:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n179:   labels:\n180:     app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube\n181:     app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}\n182: roleRef:\n183:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n184:   kind: Role\n185:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n186: subjects:\n187:   - kind: ServiceAccount\n188:     name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n189:     namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n190: ```\n191: \n192: ### WorkloadManager RBAC Schema\n193: \n194: #### ServiceAccount\n195: \n196: ```yaml\n197: apiVersion: v1\n198: kind: ServiceAccount\n199: metadata:\n200:   name: workloadmanager\n201:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n202:   labels:\n203:     app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube\n204:     app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}\n205: ```\n206: \n207: #### ClusterRole\n208: \n209: ```yaml\n210: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n211: kind: ClusterRole\n212: metadata:\n213:   name: workloadmanager\n214:   labels:\n215:     app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube\n216: rules:\n217:   - apiGroups: [\"agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n218:     resources: [\"sandboxes\"]\n219:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n220:   - apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n221:     resources: [\"sandboxclaims\", \"sandboxtemplates\", \"sandboxwarmpools\"]\n222:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n223:   - apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n224:     resources: [\"sandboxwarmpools/status\"]\n225:     verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n226:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n227:     resources: [\"codeinterpreters\"]\n228:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n229:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n230:     resources: [\"codeinterpreters/status\"]\n231:     verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n232:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n233:     resources: [\"codeinterpreters/finalizers\"]\n234:     verbs: [\"update\"]\n235:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n236:     resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]\n237:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n238:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n239:     resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\"]\n240:     verbs: [\"update\", \"patch\"]\n241:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n242:     resources: [\"pods\"]\n243:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n244:   - apiGroups: [\"authentication.k8s.io\"]\n245:     resources: [\"tokenreviews\"]\n246:     verbs: [\"create\"]\n247:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n248:     resources: [\"secrets\"]\n249:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n250: ```\n251: \n252: #### ClusterRoleBinding\n253: \n254: ```yaml\n255: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n256: kind: ClusterRoleBinding\n257: metadata:\n258:   name: workloadmanager\n259:   labels:\n260:     app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube\n261: roleRef:\n262:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n263:   kind: ClusterRole\n264:   name: workloadmanager\n265: subjects:\n266:   - kind: ServiceAccount\n267:     name: workloadmanager\n268:     namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n269: ```\n270: \n271: ### RBAC Permission Matrix\n272: \n273: #### Router Role (Namespace-scoped)\n274: \n275: | apiGroups | Resources | Verbs | Reason |\n276: |-----------|-----------|-------|--------|\n277: | `\"\"` (core) | secrets | get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete | JWT signing keys, identity secrets |\n278: \n279: #### WorkloadManager ClusterRole\n280: \n281: | apiGroups | Resources | Verbs | Reason |\n282: |-----------|-----------|-------|--------|\n283: | `agents.x-k8s.io` | sandboxes | get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete | Sandbox lifecycle management |\n284: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | sandboxclaims, sandboxtemplates, sandboxwarmpools | get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete | Extension CRD management |\n285: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | sandboxwarmpools/status | get, update, patch | WarmPool status updates |\n286: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | codeinterpreters | get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete | CodeInterpreter lifecycle |\n287: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | codeinterpreters/status | get, update, patch | Status subresource updates |\n288: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | codeinterpreters/finalizers | update | Finalizer management |\n289: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | agentruntimes | get, list, watch | AgentRuntime read access |\n290: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | agentruntimes/status | update, patch | Runtime status updates |\n291: | `\"\"` (core) | pods | get, list, watch | Pod monitoring (no create/delete) |\n292: | `\"\"` (core) | secrets | get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete | Sandbox secrets management |\n293: | `authentication.k8s.io` | tokenreviews | create | Token authentication |\n294: \n295: ### Values.yaml RBAC Configuration\n296: \n297: ```yaml\n298: router:\n299:   serviceAccountName: \"\"       # Required when router.rbac.create=true\n300:   rbac:\n301:     create: false              # Default: disabled, enable for self-contained RBAC\n302: ```\n303: \n304: ---\n305: \n306: ## API Contracts\n307: \n308: ### Router RBAC Template Contract\n309: \n310: | Field | Type | Required | Description |\n311: |-------|------|----------|-------------|\n312: | `router.rbac.create` | bool | No | Default `false`. Enable to create Router RBAC |\n313: | `router.serviceAccountName` | string | Conditional | Required when `rbac.create=true` |\n314: \n315: ### Validation Contract\n316: \n317: ```\n318: IF router.rbac.create == true AND router.serviceAccountName == \"\"\n319: THEN fail(\"router.serviceAccountName must be set when router.rbac.create is true\")\n320: ```\n321: \n322: ### Router Deployment Integration\n323: \n324: ```yaml\n325: spec:\n326:   template:\n327:     spec:\n328:       {{- if .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n329:       serviceAccountName: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n330:       {{- end }}\n331: ```\n332: \n333: ### RBAC Rendering Contract\n334: \n335: | Condition | Rendered Resources |\n336: |-----------|--------------------|\n337: | `router.rbac.create=true` | ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding |\n338: | `router.rbac.create=false` | None (user provides external RBAC) |\n339: | WorkloadManager (always) | ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding |\n340: \n341: ---\n342: \n343: ## Error Handling\n344: \n345: ### Template Validation Errors\n346: \n347: | Error | Condition | Resolution |\n348: |-------|-----------|------------|\n349: | `router.serviceAccountName must be set` | `rbac.create=true` without SA name | Set `router.serviceAccountName` in values.yaml |\n350: | `Helm lint error` | Invalid YAML syntax | Fix template syntax |\n351: | `Render error` | Undefined helper template | Verify `agentcube.labels` in `_helpers.tpl` |\n352: | `Missing namespace` | `{{ .Release.Namespace }}` undefined | Ensure Helm 3+ with namespace context |\n353: \n354: ### Template Validation Pattern\n355: \n356: ```yaml\n357: {{- if .Values.router.rbac.create }}\n358: {{- if not .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n359: {{- fail \"router.serviceAccountName must be set when router.rbac.create is true\" }}\n360: {{- end }}\n361: # RBAC resources...\n362: {{- end }}\n363: ```\n364: \n365: ### Kubernetes RBAC Errors\n366: \n367: | Error | Cause | Resolution |\n368: |-------|-------|------------|\n369: | `Forbidden` | Missing RBAC permission | Verify Role/ClusterRole rules |\n370: | `ServiceAccount not found` | SA not created | Check RBAC template rendered |\n371: | `RoleBinding references non-existent Role` | Role not created | Verify Role template |\n372: | `Cannot create cluster resource` | Namespace Role for cluster resource | Use ClusterRole for cluster-scoped resources |\n373: \n374: ### Permission Denial Patterns\n375: \n376: | Scenario | Expected Behavior | Error Message |\n377: |----------|-------------------|---------------|\n378: | Router access secret in other namespace | Forbidden | `secrets \"xxx\" is forbidden: User cannot get resource \"secrets\" in API group \"\" in namespace \"other-ns\"` |\n379: | Router create Pod | Forbidden | `pods is forbidden: User cannot create resource \"pods\"` |\n380: | WorkloadManager create Pod directly | Forbidden | `pods is forbidden: User cannot create resource \"pods\"` (only read) |\n381: | WorkloadManager delete AgentRuntime | Forbidden | `agentruntimes is forbidden: User cannot delete` (only read) |\n382: \n383: ---\n384: \n385: ## Testing Strategy\n386: \n387: ### Test Categories\n388: \n389: | Category | Scope | Tools | Purpose |\n390: |----------|-------|-------|---------|\n391: | Helm lint | Chart syntax | `helm lint` | Validate template syntax |\n392: | Template render | YAML output | `helm template` | Verify RBAC resources rendered |\n393: | Validation guard | Conditional logic | `helm template --set` | Test fail conditions |\n394: | kubectl dry-run | API schema | `kubectl apply --dry-run` | Validate Kubernetes schema |\n395: | E2E deployment | Full stack | `helm install` | Verify RBAC grants work |\n396: \n397: ### Helm Lint Test\n398: \n399: ```bash\n400: helm lint manifests/charts/base\n401: # Expected: 0 errors, 0 warnings\n402: ```\n403: \n404: ### Template Render Tests\n405: \n406: #### Test: Router RBAC enabled\n407: \n408: ```bash\n409: helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n410:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n411:   --set router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router \\\n412:   --namespace agentcube-test | grep -A20 \"kind: ServiceAccount\"\n413: \n414: # Expected: Router ServiceAccount with name \"agentcube-router\"\n415: # Expected: Router Role with secrets permissions\n416: # Expected: Router RoleBinding binding SA to Role\n417: ```\n418: \n419: #### Test: Router RBAC disabled\n420: \n421: ```bash\n422: helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n423:   --set router.rbac.create=false \\\n424:   --namespace agentcube-test | grep \"kind: Role\"\n425: \n426: # Expected: No Router Role/RoleBinding/SA (only WorkloadManager RBAC)\n427: ```\n428: \n429: #### Test: Validation guard\n430: \n431: ```bash\n432: helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n433:   --set router.rbac.create=true\n434: \n435: # Expected: Error \"router.serviceAccountName must be set\"\n436: ```\n437: \n438: ### kubectl Dry-run Tests\n439: \n440: ```bash\n441: helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n442:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n443:   --set router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router \\\n444:   --set redis.addr=\"redis:6379\" \\\n445:   > /tmp/rendered.yaml\n446: \n447: kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f /tmp/rendered.yaml\n448: # Expected: No validation errors\n449: ```\n450: \n451: ### Permission Matrix Tests\n452: \n453: | Test Case | Command | Expected |\n454: |-----------|---------|----------|\n455: | Router can read secrets | `kubectl auth can-i get secrets --as=system:serviceaccount:ns:router-sa` | `yes` |\n456: | Router cannot read pods | `kubectl auth can-i get pods --as=system:serviceaccount:ns:router-sa` | `no` |\n457: | Router cannot access other ns | `kubectl auth can-i get secrets -n other-ns --as=system:serviceaccount:ns:router-sa` | `no` |\n458: | WorkloadManager can create sandboxes | `kubectl auth can-i create sandboxes.agents.x-k8s.io --as=system:serviceaccount:ns:workloadmanager` | `yes` |\n459: | WorkloadManager can create codeinterpreters | `kubectl auth can-i create codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh --as=system:serviceaccount:ns:workloadmanager` | `yes` |\n460: | WorkloadManager cannot create pods | `kubectl auth can-i create pods --as=system:serviceaccount:ns:workloadmanager` | `no` |\n461: | WorkloadManager can create tokenreviews | `kubectl auth can-i create tokenreviews.authentication.k8s.io --as=system:serviceaccount:ns:workloadmanager` | `yes` |\n462: \n463: ### Security Audit Tests\n464: \n465: ```bash\n466: # No wildcard permissions\n467: helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n468:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n469:   --set router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router \\\n470:   | grep -E 'resources:\\s*\\[\"\\*\"\\]' | grep -E 'verbs:\\s*\\[\"\\*\"\\]'\n471: \n472: # Expected: No matches (wildcards not allowed)\n473: \n474: # No TokenReview for Router\n475: helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n476:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n477:   --set router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router \\\n478:   | grep -A5 \"kind: Role\" | grep tokenreviews\n479: \n480: # Expected: No matches (Router has no TokenReview permission)\n481: ```\n482: \n483: ### E2E Test Cases\n484: \n485: | Test | Setup | Verification |\n486: |------|-------|--------------|\n487: | Router secret lifecycle | Deploy with RBAC enabled | Router creates/reads/updates/deletes secrets in namespace |\n488: | Router namespace isolation | Deploy in ns-A, create secret in ns-B | Router access to ns-B secret fails |\n489: | WorkloadManager sandbox create | Deploy with RBAC | WorkloadManager creates Sandbox CRD |\n490: | WorkloadManager codeinterpreter lifecycle | Deploy with RBAC | WorkloadManager manages CodeInterpreter CRD |\n491: | WorkloadManager pod read | Deploy with RBAC | WorkloadManager lists pods, cannot create/delete |\n492: \n493: ### Test Commands Summary\n494: \n495: ```bash\n496: # 1. Helm lint\n497: helm lint manifests/charts/base\n498: \n499: # 2. Render with RBAC enabled\n500: helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n501:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n502:   --set router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router \\\n503:   --namespace agentcube\n504: \n505: # 3. Validation guard test\n506: helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n507:   --set router.rbac.create=true 2>&1 | grep \"serviceAccountName must be set\"\n508: \n509: # 4. Dry-run validation\n510: helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n511:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n512:   --set router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router \\\n513:   | kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f -\n514: \n515: # 5. Permission audit\n516: kubectl auth can-i --list --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:workloadmanager\n517: kubectl auth can-i --list --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:agentcube-router -n agentcube\n518: ```\n519: \n520: ---\n521: \n522: ## File Structure\n523: \n524: | Path | Role |\n525: |------|------|\n526: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` | Router ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding (conditional) |\n527: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` | WorkloadManager ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding |\n528: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/_helpers.tpl` | Named template `agentcube.labels` |\n529: | `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | `router.rbac.create`, `router.serviceAccountName` defaults |\n530: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml` | Router Deployment (uses ServiceAccount) |\n531: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml` | WorkloadManager Deployment (uses ServiceAccount) |\n532: \n533: ---\n534: \n535: ## Dependencies\n536: \n537: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n538: |---------|---------|---------|\n539: | `Kubernetes` | `>=1.24` | RBAC API stability (rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1) |\n540: | `Helm 3` | `>=3.8.0` | Template conditionals, validation guards (`fail` function) |\n541: | `agent-sandbox CRDs` | `v0.1.1` | Sandbox, SandboxClaim, SandboxTemplate, SandboxWarmPool |\n542: | `AgentCube CRDs` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | CodeInterpreter, AgentRuntime custom resources |\n543: \n544: ---\n545: \n546: ## Implementation Notes\n547: \n548: ### RBAC Scope Design\n549: \n550: | Component | Scope | Reason |\n551: |-----------|-------|--------|\n552: | Router | Namespace-scoped Role | Router only manages secrets in its namespace (JWT keys, identity) |\n553: | WorkloadManager | Cluster-scoped ClusterRole | Agent-sandbox CRDs are cluster-scoped; cross-namespace sandbox management |\n554: \n555: ### Least Privilege Principle\n556: \n557: | Resource | Verbs | Reason |\n558: |----------|-------|--------|\n559: | pods | get, list, watch | Read-only for monitoring; WorkloadManager creates via Sandbox CRD |\n560: | agentruntimes | get, list, watch | Read-only reference; no direct lifecycle management |\n561: | agentruntimes/status | update, patch | Status updates only, no delete |\n562: | sandboxwarmpools/status | get, update, patch | Status subresource pattern |\n563: | codeinterpreters/finalizers | update | Finalizer management only |\n564: | tokenreviews | create | One-shot authentication; no read/delete |\n565: \n566: ### Conditional RBAC Pattern\n567: \n568: Router RBAC is optional to support:\n569: 1. **Self-contained deployment**: `rbac.create=true` creates RBAC automatically\n570: 2. **External RBAC management**: `rbac.create=false` with pre-existing SA for IAM integration\n571: \n572: ### Namespace Isolation\n573: \n574: Router Role is explicitly namespace-scoped:\n575: - Role metadata includes `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n576: - RoleBinding binds SA within same namespace\n577: - No ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding for Router\n578: - Router cannot access secrets in other namespaces\n579: \n580: ### ServiceAccount Naming\n581: \n582: | Component | Name Source | Default |\n583: |-----------|-------------|---------|\n584: | Router | `.Values.router.serviceAccountName` | Empty (user must set) |\n585: | WorkloadManager | Fixed: `workloadmanager` | Always `workloadmanager` |\n586: \n587: ---\n588: \n589: ## References\n590: \n591: - Spec: `changes/AR-031/spec.md`\n592: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md`\n593: - Proposal: `changes/AR-031/proposal.md`\n594: - Tasks: `changes/AR-031/tasks.md`\n595: - Router RBAC Template: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n596: - WorkloadManager RBAC Template: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n597: - Helm Chart Design: `changes/AR-030/design.md`\n598: - Kubernetes RBAC Documentation: https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/access-authn-authz/rbac/\n599: - Kubernetes API Reference: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n\n(End of file - total 599 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-031 — RBAC 配置 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-031 — RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) |\n| Module | `manifests` |\n| Language | YAML |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nDefine Kubernetes RBAC resources (ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding) for AgentCube components to enable secure, least-privilege access to Kubernetes API resources. Router uses namespace-scoped Role for Secret management; WorkloadManager uses cluster-wide ClusterRole for sandbox lifecycle management and CRD operations.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Architecture\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-031/design.md","time":{"start":1775890174793,"end":1775890174830}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775890174835,"sessionID":"ses_284b2cd23ffexShxwd92QPDtT1","part":{"id":"prt_d7b4d8f8700176iF4j9tKSihW1","messageID":"msg_d7b4d5dd3001bOjiFbbK3IYzXY","sessionID":"ses_284b2cd23ffexShxwd92QPDtT1","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-39b9acb7e7724dddad280dd9911a8fe7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-031 — RBAC 配置\n2: \n3: **Module:** `manifests`  \n4: **Language:** YAML  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Define Kubernetes RBAC resources (ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding) for AgentCube components to enable secure, least-privilege access to Kubernetes API resources. Router uses namespace-scoped Role for Secret management; WorkloadManager uses cluster-wide ClusterRole for sandbox lifecycle management and CRD operations.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Router RBAC template\n18: \n19: The system SHALL provide namespace-scoped RBAC resources for Router with conditional creation and validation.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Router RBAC conditional rendering\n22: - **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` exists\n23: - **WHEN** `{{ .Values.router.rbac.create }}` is `true`\n24: - **THEN** ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding SHALL be rendered\n25: - **WHEN** value is `false`\n26: - **THEN** no RBAC resources SHALL be rendered for router\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: Router serviceAccountName validation guard\n29: - **GIVEN** Router RBAC is enabled (`router.rbac.create: true`)\n30: - **WHEN** `{{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}` is empty or not set\n31: - **THEN** template SHALL fail with error: `\"router.serviceAccountName must be set when router.rbac.create is true\"`\n32: - **WHEN** value is set\n33: - **THEN** template SHALL render successfully\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Router ServiceAccount creation\n36: - **GIVEN** Router RBAC is enabled\n37: - **WHEN** ServiceAccount is templated\n38: - **THEN** ServiceAccount SHALL have:\n39:   - `apiVersion: v1`\n40:   - `kind: ServiceAccount`\n41:   - `name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}`\n42:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n43:   - `labels` from helper template `agentcube.labels`\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Router Role namespace-scoped permissions\n46: - **GIVEN** Router needs Secret access within its namespace\n47: - **WHEN** Role is templated\n48: - **THEN** Role SHALL have:\n49:   - `apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1`\n50:   - `kind: Role`\n51:   - `name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}`\n52:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n53:   - `rules` array with single entry:\n54:     - `apiGroups: [\"\"]` (core API group)\n55:     - `resources: [\"secrets\"]`\n56:     - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\",\"create\",\"update\",\"patch\",\"delete\"]`\n57: \n58: #### Scenario: Router RoleBinding binding\n59: - **GIVEN** Router Role needs binding to ServiceAccount\n60: - **WHEN** RoleBinding is templated\n61: - **THEN** RoleBinding SHALL have:\n62:   - `apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1`\n63:   - `kind: RoleBinding`\n64:   - `name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}`\n65:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n66:   - `labels` from helper template\n67:   - `subjects`: ServiceAccount with name from values in release namespace\n68:   - `roleRef`:\n69:     - `apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io`\n70:     - `kind: Role`\n71:     - `name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}`\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: Router RBAC no cluster-wide access\n74: - **GIVEN** Router Role only grants namespace-scoped permissions\n75: - **WHEN** Role rules are evaluated\n76: - **THEN** no ClusterRole or ClusterRoleBinding SHALL be created for Router\n77: - **AND** Router SHALL NOT have access to resources in other namespaces\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ### Requirement: WorkloadManager RBAC template\n82: \n83: The system SHALL provide cluster-wide RBAC resources for WorkloadManager with full CRD operation permissions.\n84: \n85: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ServiceAccount creation\n86: - **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` is rendered\n87: - **WHEN** helm template executes\n88: - **THEN** ServiceAccount SHALL have:\n89:   - `apiVersion: v1`\n90:   - `kind: ServiceAccount`\n91:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n92:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n93:   - `labels` from helper template `agentcube.labels`\n94: \n95: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole agent-sandbox permissions\n96: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs Sandbox CRD access\n97: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules for `agents.x-k8s.io` are defined\n98: - **THEN** ClusterRole SHALL grant:\n99:   - `apiGroups: [\"agents.x-k8s.io\"]`\n100:   - `resources: [\"sandboxes\"]`\n101:   - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\",\"create\",\"update\",\"patch\",\"delete\"]`\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole sandbox extension permissions\n104: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs extension CRD access\n105: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules for `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` are defined\n106: - **THEN** ClusterRole SHALL grant:\n107:   - `apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]`\n108:   - `resources: [\"sandboxclaims\",\"sandboxtemplates\",\"sandboxwarmpools\"]`\n109:   - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\",\"create\",\"update\",\"patch\",\"delete\"]`\n110:   - `resources: [\"sandboxwarmpools/status\"]`\n111:   - `verbs: [\"get\",\"update\",\"patch\"]`\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole CodeInterpreter permissions\n114: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs CodeInterpreter CRD access\n115: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` are defined\n116: - **THEN** ClusterRole SHALL grant:\n117:   - `apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]`\n118:   - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters\"]`\n119:   - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\",\"create\",\"update\",\"patch\",\"delete\"]`\n120:   - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters/status\"]`\n121:   - `verbs: [\"get\",\"update\",\"patch\"]`\n122:   - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters/finalizers\"]`\n123:   - `verbs: [\"update\"]`\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole AgentRuntime permissions\n126: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs AgentRuntime CRD read access\n127: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules for AgentRuntime are defined\n128: - **THEN** ClusterRole SHALL grant:\n129:   - `apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]`\n130:   - `resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]`\n131:   - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\"]`\n132:   - `resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\"]`\n133:   - `verbs: [\"update\",\"patch\"]`\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole core resource permissions\n136: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs Pod and Secret access\n137: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules for core API are defined\n138: - **THEN** ClusterRole SHALL grant:\n139:   - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n140:   - `resources: [\"pods\"]`\n141:   - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\"]`\n142:   - `resources: [\"secrets\"]`\n143:   - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\",\"create\",\"update\",\"patch\",\"delete\"]`\n144: \n145: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole TokenReview permission\n146: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs TokenReview for authentication\n147: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules for authentication API are defined\n148: - **THEN** ClusterRole SHALL grant:\n149:   - `apiGroups: [\"authentication.k8s.io\"]`\n150:   - `resources: [\"tokenreviews\"]`\n151:   - `verbs: [\"create\"]`\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding creation\n154: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager ClusterRole needs binding\n155: - **WHEN** ClusterRoleBinding is templated\n156: - **THEN** ClusterRoleBinding SHALL have:\n157:   - `apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1`\n158:   - `kind: ClusterRoleBinding`\n159:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n160:   - `labels` from helper template\n161:   - `subjects`:\n162:     - `kind: ServiceAccount`\n163:     - `name: workloadmanager`\n164:     - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n165:   - `roleRef`:\n166:     - `apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io`\n167:     - `kind: ClusterRole`\n168:     - `name: workloadmanager`\n169: \n170: ---\n171: \n172: ### Requirement: RBAC values.yaml configuration\n173: \n174: The system SHALL provide configurable RBAC flags in values.yaml.\n175: \n176: #### Scenario: Router RBAC create flag default\n177: - **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` defines router section\n178: - **WHEN** `router.rbac.create` is defined\n179: - **THEN** default value SHALL be `false` (RBAC disabled by default)\n180: \n181: #### Scenario: Router serviceAccountName configuration\n182: - **GIVEN** router RBAC can be enabled\n183: - **WHEN** `router.serviceAccountName` is defined in values.yaml\n184: - **THEN** default value SHALL be `\"\"` (empty string, user must set when enabling RBAC)\n185: \n186: #### Scenario: Router RBAC enabled deployment\n187: - **GIVEN** user wants Router RBAC created by Helm\n188: - **WHEN** values.yaml is configured with:\n189:   - `router.rbac.create: true`\n190:   - `router.serviceAccountName: \"agentcube-router\"`\n191: - **THEN** Helm install SHALL create ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding\n192: - **AND** Router Deployment SHALL use `serviceAccountName: agentcube-router`\n193: \n194: #### Scenario: Router external RBAC deployment\n195: - **GIVEN** user has pre-existing ServiceAccount/RBAC externally managed\n196: - **WHEN** values.yaml is configured with:\n197:   - `router.rbac.create: false`\n198:   - `router.serviceAccountName: \"my-existing-sa\"`\n199: - **THEN** Helm install SHALL NOT create RBAC resources\n200: - **AND** Router Deployment SHALL reference existing ServiceAccount\n201: \n202: ---\n203: \n204: ### Requirement: RBAC security compliance\n205: \n206: The system SHALL follow Kubernetes RBAC best practices with minimal permission grants.\n207: \n208: #### Scenario: No wildcard permissions\n209: - **GIVEN** RBAC templates define permission rules\n210: - **WHEN** ClusterRole or Role rules are inspected\n211: - **THEN** no rule SHALL use wildcard `\"*\"` for `resources` or `verbs`\n212: - **AND** all `apiGroups`, `resources`, `verbs` SHALL be explicitly listed\n213: \n214: #### Scenario: Least privilege principle\n215: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs specific operations on resources\n216: - **WHEN** ClusterRole verbs are defined per resource\n217: - **THEN** verbs SHALL be minimum required for operation:\n218:   - Read-only resources: `get`, `list`, `watch` only\n219:   - Status subresources: `get`, `update`, `patch` only (no delete)\n220:   - Finalizers: `update` only\n221:   - Managed resources: full CRUD where lifecycle management required\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: Namespace isolation for Router\n224: - **GIVEN** Router only needs secrets in its own namespace\n225: - **WHEN** Router Role is evaluated\n226: - **THEN** Role SHALL NOT grant access to cluster-wide resources\n227: - **AND** Role SHALL NOT grant access to resources in other namespaces\n228: - **AND** RoleBinding SHALL only bind within `{{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: TokenReview restricted to WorkloadManager\n231: - **GIVEN** TokenReview is sensitive authentication operation\n232: - **WHEN** RBAC permissions are audited\n233: - **THEN** TokenReview `create` verb SHALL only be granted to WorkloadManager\n234: - **AND** Router SHALL NOT have TokenReview permission\n235: \n236: ---\n237: \n238: ### Requirement: RBAC template validation\n239: \n240: The system SHALL provide template validation for RBAC configuration.\n241: \n242: #### Scenario: Helm template rendering validation\n243: - **GIVEN** RBAC templates are complete\n244: - **WHEN** `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router` is executed\n245: - **THEN** output SHALL contain valid YAML for:\n246:   - Router ServiceAccount\n247:   - Router Role\n248:   - Router RoleBinding\n249:   - WorkloadManager ServiceAccount\n250:   - WorkloadManager ClusterRole\n251:   - WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding\n252: \n253: #### Scenario: Helm template failure on missing serviceAccountName\n254: - **GIVEN** Router RBAC is enabled\n255: - **WHEN** `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set router.rbac.create=true` is executed without `router.serviceAccountName`\n256: - **THEN** template SHALL fail with error message containing `\"router.serviceAccountName must be set\"`\n257: \n258: #### Scenario: Helm template skip when RBAC disabled\n259: - **GIVEN** Router RBAC is disabled\n260: - **WHEN** `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set router.rbac.create=false` is executed\n261: - **THEN** output SHALL NOT contain Router ServiceAccount, Role, or RoleBinding\n262: - **AND** WorkloadManager RBAC SHALL still be rendered\n263: \n264: #### Scenario: Helm lint passes\n265: - **GIVEN** RBAC templates are complete\n266: - **WHEN** `helm lint manifests/charts/base` is executed\n267: - **THEN** lint SHALL pass with no errors related to RBAC templates\n268: \n269: ---\n270: \n271: ### Requirement: E2E RBAC validation\n272: \n273: The system SHALL validate RBAC permissions in E2E tests.\n274: \n275: #### Scenario: E2E Router secret access\n276: - **GIVEN** Router RBAC is deployed with `router.rbac.create=true`\n277: - **WHEN** Router Pod attempts to create/read/update/delete Secret in its namespace\n278: - **THEN** operations SHALL succeed (permission granted by Role)\n279: - **WHEN** Router Pod attempts to access Secret in different namespace\n280: - **THEN** operation SHALL fail (namespace isolation)\n281: \n282: #### Scenario: E2E WorkloadManager sandbox creation\n283: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager RBAC is deployed\n284: - **WHEN** WorkloadManager Pod attempts to create Sandbox CRD\n285: - **THEN** operation SHALL succeed (permission granted by ClusterRole)\n286: - **WHEN** WorkloadManager Pod attempts to update Sandbox status\n287: - **THEN** operation SHALL succeed\n288: \n289: #### Scenario: E2E WorkloadManager CodeInterpreter lifecycle\n290: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager RBAC is deployed\n291: - **WHEN** WorkloadManager Pod attempts full lifecycle on CodeInterpreter CRD\n292: - **THEN** create, get, list, update, delete SHALL succeed\n293: - **WHEN** WorkloadManager Pod attempts to update CodeInterpreter finalizers\n294: - **THEN** operation SHALL succeed\n295: \n296: #### Scenario: E2E WorkloadManager Pod read access\n297: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager RBAC is deployed\n298: - **WHEN** WorkloadManager Pod attempts to get/list/watch Pods\n299: - **THEN** operations SHALL succeed\n300: - **WHEN** WorkloadManager Pod attempts to create/delete Pod directly\n301: - **THEN** operation SHALL fail (only read verbs granted)\n302: \n303: ---\n304: \n305: ## Constants Summary\n306: \n307: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n308: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n309: | `ROUTER_RBAC_CREATE_DEFAULT` | `false` | `values.yaml` | Router RBAC disabled by default |\n310: | `ROUTER_SA_NAME_DEFAULT` | `\"\"` | `values.yaml` | Router ServiceAccount name must be explicitly set |\n311: | `WORKLOADMANAGER_SA_NAME` | `workloadmanager` | `rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` | Fixed ServiceAccount name for WorkloadManager |\n312: | `RBAC_API_VERSION` | `rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1` | RBAC templates | Stable RBAC API version |\n313: \n314: ---\n315: \n316: ## Dependencies Summary\n317: \n318: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n319: |---------|---------|---------|\n320: | `Kubernetes` | `>=1.24` | RBAC API stability (rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1) |\n321: | `Helm 3` | `>=3.8.0` | Template conditionals and validation guards |\n322: | `agent-sandbox CRDs` | `agents.x-k8s.io` | Sandbox, SandboxClaim, SandboxTemplate, SandboxWarmPool resources |\n323: | `AgentCube CRDs` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | CodeInterpreter, AgentRuntime custom resources |\n324: \n325: ---\n326: \n327: ## File Changes Summary\n328: \n329: | File | Action | Description |\n330: |------|--------|-------------|\n331: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` | Modified | Add validation guard for serviceAccountName requirement |\n332: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` | Existing | WorkloadManager RBAC resources (no changes) |\n333: | `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | Modified | Document `router.rbac.create` and `router.serviceAccountName` defaults |\n334: \n335: ---\n336: \n337: ## References\n338: \n339: - proposal.md — AR-031 proposal with scope and implementation checklist\n340: - manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml — Router RBAC template\n341: - manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml — WorkloadManager RBAC template\n342: - Kubernetes RBAC Documentation — https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/access-authn-authz/rbac/\n343: - changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md — Helm Chart templates context\n344: \n345: ---\n346: \n347: ## Validation Checklist\n348: \n349: - [ ] `helm lint manifests/charts/base` passes with no errors\n350: - [ ] Router RBAC renders when `router.rbac.create=true` with valid `serviceAccountName`\n351: - [ ] Router RBAC skipped when `router.rbac.create=false`\n352: - [ ] Template fails when `router.rbac.create=true` without `serviceAccountName`\n353: - [ ] Router Role only grants Secret permissions (namespace-scoped)\n354: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole grants all required CRD permissions\n355: - [ ] No wildcard (`*`) in any RBAC resources or verbs\n356: - [ ] TokenReview only granted to WorkloadManager, not Router\n357: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding references correct ServiceAccount\n358: - [ ] E2E test: Router can manage secrets in its namespace\n359: - [ ] E2E test: WorkloadManager can create/manage Sandboxes\n360: - [ ] E2E test: WorkloadManager can create/manage CodeInterpreters\n\n(End of file - total 360 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-031 — RBAC 配置\n\n**Module:** `manifests`  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine Kubernetes RBAC resources (ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding) for AgentCube components to enable secure, least-privilege access to Kubernetes API resources. Router uses namespace-scoped Role for Secret management; WorkloadManager uses cluster-wide ClusterRole for sandbox lifecycle management and CRD operations.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Router RBAC template\n\nThe system SHALL provide namespace-scoped RBAC resources for Router with conditional creation and validation.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775890174796,"end":1775890174833}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775890174839,"sessionID":"ses_284b2cd23ffexShxwd92QPDtT1","part":{"id":"prt_d7b4d9327001KHRxWsRKE3L8U4","messageID":"msg_d7b4d5dd3001bOjiFbbK3IYzXY","sessionID":"ses_284b2cd23ffexShxwd92QPDtT1","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-8997f34e00a2414bb491fef04d311252","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-031/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-031/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-031 — RBAC 配置 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-031 — RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) |\n8: | Module | `manifests` |\n9: | Language | YAML |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Router RBAC Foundation (ST-1)\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1**: Create Router ServiceAccount template with conditional rendering\n20:   - Purpose: Define ServiceAccount when `router.rbac.create=true`\n21:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n22:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router | grep \"kind: ServiceAccount\" | grep \"name: agentcube-router\"`\n23: \n24: - [ ] **T1.2**: Implement Router ServiceAccount validation guard\n25:   - Purpose: Fail if `router.rbac.create=true` but `router.serviceAccountName` not set\n26:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n27:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true 2>&1 | grep \"serviceAccountName must be set\"`\n28: \n29: - [ ] **T1.3**: Define Router Role with namespace-scoped secrets permissions\n30:   - Purpose: Create Role with `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` for secrets\n31:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n32:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep -A10 \"kind: Role\" | grep \"secrets\"`\n33: \n34: - [ ] **T1.4**: Create Router RoleBinding to bind ServiceAccount to Role\n35:   - Purpose: Establish SA → Role binding within namespace\n36:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n37:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep -A10 \"kind: RoleBinding\"`\n38: \n39: - [ ] **T1.5**: Implement Router Role namespace isolation\n40:   - Purpose: Ensure Role and RoleBinding are namespace-scoped (not cluster-wide)\n41:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n42:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa --namespace agentcube | grep \"namespace: agentcube\"`\n43: \n44: ### Phase 2: WorkloadManager RBAC (ST-2)\n45: \n46: - [ ] **T2.1**: Create WorkloadManager ServiceAccount template\n47:   - Purpose: Define ServiceAccount for WorkloadManager (cluster-scoped identity)\n48:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n49:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep \"kind: ServiceAccount\" | grep \"name: workloadmanager\"`\n50: \n51: - [ ] **T2.2**: Define WorkloadManager ClusterRole for agents.x-k8s.io CRDs\n52:   - Purpose: Grant permissions for `sandboxes` (full CRUD)\n53:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n54:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A15 \"kind: ClusterRole\" | grep \"sandboxes\"`\n55: \n56: - [ ] **T2.3**: Define WorkloadManager ClusterRole for extensions.agents.x-k8s.io CRDs\n57:   - Purpose: Grant permissions for `sandboxclaims`, `sandboxtemplates`, `sandboxwarmpools` and status subresource\n58:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n59:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A15 \"kind: ClusterRole\" | grep \"sandboxclaims\"`\n60: \n61: - [ ] **T2.4**: Define WorkloadManager ClusterRole for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh CRDs\n62:   - Purpose: Grant full CRUD for `codeinterpreters` + status/finalizers, read-only for `agentruntimes` + status updates\n63:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n64:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A20 \"kind: ClusterRole\" | grep \"codeinterpreters\"`\n65: \n66: - [ ] **T2.5**: Define WorkloadManager ClusterRole for core Kubernetes resources\n67:   - Purpose: Grant read-only for `pods`, full CRUD for `secrets`\n68:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n69:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A25 \"kind: ClusterRole\" | grep \"pods\"`\n70: \n71: - [ ] **T2.6**: Define WorkloadManager ClusterRole for TokenReview\n72:   - Purpose: Grant `create` permission for `authentication.k8s.io/tokenreviews`\n73:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n74:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A30 \"kind: ClusterRole\" | grep \"tokenreviews\"`\n75: \n76: - [ ] **T2.7**: Create WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding\n77:   - Purpose: Bind ClusterRole to ServiceAccount (cluster-wide binding)\n78:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n79:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A10 \"kind: ClusterRoleBinding\"`\n80: \n81: ### Phase 3: Deployment Integration (ST-3)\n82: \n83: - [ ] **T3.1**: Integrate Router ServiceAccount into Router Deployment\n84:   - Purpose: Set `serviceAccountName` in Router Deployment spec when `router.serviceAccountName` is provided\n85:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n86:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep \"serviceAccountName: test-sa\"`\n87: \n88: - [ ] **T3.2**: Integrate WorkloadManager ServiceAccount into WorkloadManager Deployment\n89:   - Purpose: Set fixed `serviceAccountName: workloadmanager` in WorkloadManager Deployment\n90:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml`\n91:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A5 \"name: workloadmanager\" | grep \"serviceAccountName: workloadmanager\"`\n92: \n93: - [ ] **T3.3**: Update values.yaml with router.rbac.create configuration\n94:   - Purpose: Add `router.rbac.create: false` default and `router.serviceAccountName: \"\"` default\n95:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml`\n96:   - Verification: `grep \"rbac:\" manifests/charts/base/values.yaml && grep \"create: false\" manifests/charts/base/values.yaml`\n97: \n98: ### Phase 4: Permission Validation (ST-4)\n99: \n100: - [ ] **T4.1**: Verify Router Role has no wildcard permissions\n101:   - Purpose: Ensure no `*` in resources or verbs (least-privilege compliance)\n102:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n103:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep -E 'resources:\\s*\\[\"\\*\"\\]' | grep -E 'verbs:\\s*\\[\"\\*\"\\]' || echo \"OK\"`\n104: \n105: - [ ] **T4.2**: Verify Router Role has no TokenReview permission\n106:   - Purpose: Router should only have secrets access (no authentication API)\n107:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n108:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep -A5 \"kind: Role\" | grep \"tokenreviews\" || echo \"OK\"`\n109: \n110: - [ ] **T4.3**: Verify WorkloadManager ClusterRole has no Pod create/delete permissions\n111:   - Purpose: WorkloadManager creates pods via Sandbox CRD, not directly\n112:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n113:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A5 \"pods\" | grep -E \"(create|delete)\" || echo \"OK\"`\n114: \n115: - [ ] **T4.4**: Verify WorkloadManager ClusterRole has no AgentRuntime delete permission\n116:   - Purpose: WorkloadManager only reads AgentRuntimes, cannot delete\n117:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n118:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A5 \"agentruntimes\" | grep \"delete\" || echo \"OK\"`\n119: \n120: - [ ] **T4.5**: Verify all ClusterRole rules use correct API groups\n121:   - Purpose: Validate API groups: `agents.x-k8s.io`, `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io`, `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, `authentication.k8s.io`, core `\"\"`\n122:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n123:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A50 \"kind: ClusterRole\" | grep \"apiGroups\"`\n124: \n125: ### Phase 5: Helm Chart Validation Tests (ST-5)\n126: \n127: - [ ] **T5.1**: Run Helm lint on chart with RBAC enabled\n128:   - Purpose: Validate chart syntax with Router RBAC enabled\n129:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/`\n130:   - Verification: `helm lint manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa`\n131: \n132: - [ ] **T5.2**: Test Router RBAC disabled scenario\n133:   - Purpose: Verify no Router RBAC resources rendered when `router.rbac.create=false`\n134:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n135:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=false | grep \"kind: Role\" || echo \"OK\"`\n136: \n137: - [ ] **T5.3**: Test Router RBAC validation guard failure\n138:   - Purpose: Verify template fails when `router.rbac.create=true` without serviceAccountName\n139:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n140:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true 2>&1 | grep \"serviceAccountName must be set\"`\n141: \n142: - [ ] **T5.4**: Test Router RBAC rendering with custom namespace\n143:   - Purpose: Verify RBAC resources use correct namespace from Helm release\n144:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n145:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa --namespace agentcube | grep \"namespace: agentcube\"`\n146: \n147: - [ ] **T5.5**: Test WorkloadManager RBAC always rendered\n148:   - Purpose: Verify WorkloadManager RBAC renders regardless of Router RBAC setting\n149:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n150:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=false | grep \"kind: ClusterRole\"`\n151: \n152: ### Phase 6: Kubernetes API Validation Tests (ST-6)\n153: \n154: - [ ] **T6.1**: Validate Router RBAC resources with kubectl dry-run\n155:   - Purpose: Verify Router RBAC YAML is valid Kubernetes schema\n156:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/`\n157:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa > /tmp/router-rbac.yaml && kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f /tmp/router-rbac.yaml | grep \"serviceaccount\"`\n158: \n159: - [ ] **T6.2**: Validate WorkloadManager RBAC resources with kubectl dry-run\n160:   - Purpose: Verify WorkloadManager RBAC YAML is valid Kubernetes schema\n161:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/`\n162:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" > /tmp/workloadmanager-rbac.yaml && kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f /tmp/workloadmanager-rbac.yaml | grep \"clusterrole\"`\n163: \n164: - [ ] **T6.3**: Validate complete chart with kubectl dry-run\n165:   - Purpose: Verify entire rendered chart is valid for Kubernetes API\n166:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/`\n167:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa > /tmp/rendered.yaml && kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f /tmp/rendered.yaml`\n168: \n169: ### Phase 7: Permission Matrix Tests (ST-7)\n170: \n171: - [ ] **T7.1**: Test Router ServiceAccount can access secrets in own namespace\n172:   - Purpose: Verify `kubectl auth can-i` returns `yes` for Router SA secrets access\n173:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n174:   - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i get secrets --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:agentcube-router -n agentcube` (expected: yes)\n175: \n176: - [ ] **T7.2**: Test Router ServiceAccount cannot access secrets in other namespace\n177:   - Purpose: Verify namespace isolation - Router SA forbidden in other namespaces\n178:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n179:   - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i get secrets -n other-ns --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:agentcube-router` (expected: no)\n180: \n181: - [ ] **T7.3**: Test Router ServiceAccount cannot create pods\n182:   - Purpose: Verify Router has no pod creation permission\n183:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n184:   - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i create pods --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:agentcube-router -n agentcube` (expected: no)\n185: \n186: - [ ] **T7.4**: Test WorkloadManager ServiceAccount can create sandboxes\n187:   - Purpose: Verify WorkloadManager has sandbox creation permission\n188:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n189:   - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i create sandboxes.agents.x-k8s.io --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:workloadmanager` (expected: yes)\n190: \n191: - [ ] **T7.5**: Test WorkloadManager ServiceAccount can create codeinterpreters\n192:   - Purpose: Verify WorkloadManager has CodeInterpreter CRD permissions\n193:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n194:   - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i create codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:workloadmanager` (expected: yes)\n195: \n196: - [ ] **T7.6**: Test WorkloadManager ServiceAccount cannot create pods directly\n197:   - Purpose: Verify WorkloadManager cannot create Pods (only via Sandbox CRD)\n198:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n199:   - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i create pods --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:workloadmanager` (expected: no)\n200: \n201: - [ ] **T7.7**: Test WorkloadManager ServiceAccount can create TokenReviews\n202:   - Purpose: Verify TokenReview create permission for authentication\n203:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n204:   - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i create tokenreviews.authentication.k8s.io --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:workloadmanager` (expected: yes)\n205: \n206: - [ ] **T7.8**: Test WorkloadManager ServiceAccount cannot delete AgentRuntimes\n207:   - Purpose: Verify AgentRuntime is read-only for WorkloadManager\n208:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n209:   - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i delete agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:workloadmanager` (expected: no)\n210: \n211: ### Phase 8: Security Audit Tests (ST-8)\n212: \n213: - [ ] **T8.1**: Verify no ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding for Router\n214:   - Purpose: Router should only have namespace-scoped Role (not cluster-wide)\n215:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n216:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep \"kind: ClusterRole\" || echo \"OK\"`\n217: \n218: - [ ] **T8.2**: Verify Router Role metadata includes namespace\n219:   - Purpose: Confirm Role is namespace-scoped (not cluster-scoped)\n220:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n221:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa --namespace agentcube | grep -A3 \"kind: Role\" | grep \"namespace\"`\n222: \n223: - [ ] **T8.3**: Verify WorkloadManager ClusterRole has least-privilege verbs for pods\n224:   - Purpose: Pods should only have `get,list,watch` (no create/update/delete)\n225:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n226:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A8 \"pods\" | grep -E \"(create|update|patch|delete)\" || echo \"OK\"`\n227: \n228: - [ ] **T8.4**: Verify WorkloadManager ClusterRole has least-privilege verbs for agentruntimes\n229:   - Purpose: AgentRuntimes should only have `get,list,watch` (no create/delete)\n230:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n231:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A8 \"agentruntimes\" | grep \"verbs\" | grep -E \"(create|delete)\" || echo \"OK\"`\n232: \n233: - [ ] **T8.5**: Verify no wildcard `*` permissions in any RBAC rule\n234:   - Purpose: Security audit - wildcards violate least-privilege principle\n235:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/`\n236:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep -E 'verbs:\\s*\\[\"\\*\"\\]' || echo \"OK\"`\n237: \n238: ---\n239: \n240: ## Task Dependencies\n241: \n242: ```\n243: Phase 1 (Router RBAC Foundation) ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n244: T1.1 (SA) ──┬── T1.2 (validation guard)\n245:             ├── T1.3 (Role)\n246:             ├── T1.4 (RoleBinding)\n247:             └── T1.5 (namespace isolation)\n248: \n249: Phase 2 (WorkloadManager RBAC) ───────────────────────────────────────────────\n250: T2.1 (SA) ──┬── T2.2 (agents.x-k8s.io)\n251:             ├── T2.3 (extensions.agents.x-k8s.io)\n252:             ├── T2.4 (runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh)\n253:             ├── T2.5 (core resources)\n254:             ├── T2.6 (TokenReview)\n255:             └── T2.7 (ClusterRoleBinding)\n256: \n257: Phase 3 (Deployment Integration) ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n258: T1.1-T1.5 ──┬── T3.1 (Router Deployment)\n259: T2.1-T2.7 ──┬── T3.2 (WorkloadManager Deployment)\n260:             └── T3.3 (values.yaml)\n261: \n262: Phase 4 (Permission Validation) ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n263: T1.1-T3.3 ──┬── T4.1-T4.5 (permission matrix validation)\n264: \n265: Phase 5 (Helm Validation) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n266: T1.1-T4.5 ──┬── T5.1-T5.5 (Helm template tests)\n267: \n268: Phase 6 (Kubernetes API Validation) ──────────────────────────────────────────\n269: T5.1-T5.5 ──┬── T6.1-T6.3 (kubectl dry-run tests)\n270: \n271: Phase 7 (Permission Matrix Tests) ────────────────────────────────────────────\n272: T6.1-T6.3 ──┬── T7.1-T7.8 (kubectl auth can-i tests) [requires cluster]\n273: \n274: Phase 8 (Security Audit) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n275: T1.1-T7.8 ──┬── T8.1-T8.5 (security audit checks)\n276: ```\n277: \n278: ---\n279: \n280: ## Verification Commands\n281: \n282: | Task Phase | Verification Command |\n283: |------------|----------------------|\n284: | Phase 1 | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep -A10 \"kind: ServiceAccount\" \\| grep \"name: test-sa\"` |\n285: | Phase 2 | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A50 \"kind: ClusterRole\" \\| grep \"sandboxes\"` |\n286: | Phase 3 | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep \"serviceAccountName: test-sa\"` |\n287: | Phase 4 | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep -E 'verbs:\\s*\\[\"\\*\"\\]' || echo \"OK\"` |\n288: | Phase 5 | `helm lint manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa` |\n289: | Phase 6 | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" > /tmp/rendered.yaml && kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f /tmp/rendered.yaml` |\n290: | Phase 7 | `kubectl auth can-i create sandboxes.agents.x-k8s.io --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:workloadmanager` (requires cluster deployment) |\n291: | Phase 8 | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep \"kind: ClusterRole\" \\| grep -v workloadmanager || echo \"OK\"` |\n292: \n293: ---\n294: \n295: ## Acceptance Criteria\n296: \n297: - [ ] Router ServiceAccount rendered when `router.rbac.create=true`\n298: - [ ] Router Role has namespace-scoped secrets permissions (get/list/watch/create/update/patch/delete)\n299: - [ ] Router RoleBinding binds Router SA to Router Role within namespace\n300: - [ ] Router RBAC validation guard: fail if `router.rbac.create=true` without `router.serviceAccountName`\n301: - [ ] Router RBAC not rendered when `router.rbac.create=false`\n302: - [ ] Router RBAC has no cluster-scoped resources (no ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding)\n303: - [ ] Router RBAC uses correct namespace from `{{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n304: - [ ] WorkloadManager ServiceAccount always rendered\n305: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has permissions for agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxes (full CRUD)\n306: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has permissions for extensions.agents.x-k8s.io (sandboxclaims, sandboxtemplates, sandboxwarmpools + status)\n307: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has permissions for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters (full CRUD + status/finalizers)\n308: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has permissions for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/agentruntimes (read-only + status updates)\n309: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has permissions for core pods (read-only: get/list/watch)\n310: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has permissions for core secrets (full CRUD)\n311: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has permission for authentication.k8s.io/tokenreviews (create only)\n312: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding binds WM SA to WM ClusterRole\n313: - [ ] Router Deployment uses `router.serviceAccountName` when provided\n314: - [ ] WorkloadManager Deployment uses fixed `serviceAccountName: workloadmanager`\n315: - [ ] values.yaml includes `router.rbac.create: false` default\n316: - [ ] values.yaml includes `router.serviceAccountName: \"\"` default\n317: - [ ] Helm lint passes with 0 errors\n318: - [ ] Rendered YAML validates with kubectl dry-run\n319: - [ ] Router SA can access secrets in own namespace (kubectl auth can-i)\n320: - [ ] Router SA cannot access secrets in other namespaces (namespace isolation)\n321: - [ ] Router SA cannot create pods (least-privilege)\n322: - [ ] WorkloadManager SA can create sandboxes CRDs\n323: - [ ] WorkloadManager SA can create codeinterpreter CRDs\n324: - [ ] WorkloadManager SA cannot create pods directly (only via Sandbox)\n325: - [ ] WorkloadManager SA cannot delete agentruntimes (read-only)\n326: - [ ] WorkloadManager SA can create TokenReviews\n327: - [ ] No wildcard `*` permissions in any RBAC rule\n328: - [ ] Router Role has no TokenReview permission\n329: - [ ] All RBAC rules use correct API groups\n330: \n331: ---\n332: \n333: ## File Changes Summary\n334: \n335: | File | Action | Lines | Description |\n336: |------|--------|-------|-------------|\n337: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` | Create | 49 | Router RBAC (ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding - conditional rendering) |\n338: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` | Create | 131 | WorkloadManager RBAC (ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding) |\n339: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml` | Modify | 81 | Add serviceAccountName field integration |\n340: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml` | Modify | - | Add serviceAccountName: workloadmanager (if missing) |\n341: | `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | Modify | 57 | Add router.rbac.create and router.serviceAccountName defaults |\n342: \n343: ---\n344: \n345: ## Implementation Notes\n346: \n347: ### Router RBAC Conditional Rendering Pattern\n348: \n349: ```yaml\n350: {{- if .Values.router.rbac.create }}\n351: {{- if not .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n352: {{- fail \"router.serviceAccountName must be set when router.rbac.create is true\" }}\n353: {{- end }}\n354: apiVersion: v1\n355: kind: ServiceAccount\n356: metadata:\n357:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n358:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n359:   labels:\n360:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n361: ---\n362: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n363: kind: Role\n364: metadata:\n365:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n366:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n367:   labels:\n368:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n369: rules:\n370:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n371:     resources: [\"secrets\"]\n372:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n373: ---\n374: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n375: kind: RoleBinding\n376: metadata:\n377:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n378:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n379:   labels:\n380:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n381: roleRef:\n382:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n383:   kind: Role\n384:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n385: subjects:\n386:   - kind: ServiceAccount\n387:     name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n388:     namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n389: {{- end }}\n390: ```\n391: \n392: ### WorkloadManager ClusterRole Permission Matrix\n393: \n394: ```yaml\n395: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n396: kind: ClusterRole\n397: metadata:\n398:   name: workloadmanager\n399: rules:\n400:   - apiGroups: [\"agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n401:     resources: [\"sandboxes\"]\n402:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n403:   \n404:   - apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n405:     resources: [\"sandboxclaims\", \"sandboxtemplates\", \"sandboxwarmpools\"]\n406:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n407:   \n408:   - apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n409:     resources: [\"sandboxwarmpools/status\"]\n410:     verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n411:   \n412:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n413:     resources: [\"codeinterpreters\"]\n414:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n415:   \n416:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n417:     resources: [\"codeinterpreters/status\", \"codeinterpreters/finalizers\"]\n418:     verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n419:   \n420:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n421:     resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]\n422:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n423:   \n424:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n425:     resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\"]\n426:     verbs: [\"update\", \"patch\"]\n427:   \n428:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n429:     resources: [\"pods\"]\n430:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n431:   \n432:   - apiGroups: [\"authentication.k8s.io\"]\n433:     resources: [\"tokenreviews\"]\n434:     verbs: [\"create\"]\n435:   \n436:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n437:     resources: [\"secrets\"]\n438:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n439: ```\n440: \n441: ### RBAC Scope Design Rationale\n442: \n443: | Component | Scope | Reason |\n444: |-----------|-------|--------|\n445: | Router | Namespace-scoped (Role/RoleBinding) | Router only manages secrets in its namespace (JWT signing keys, identity secrets). No cluster-wide access needed. |\n446: | WorkloadManager | Cluster-scoped (ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding) | Agent-sandbox CRDs are cluster-scoped; WorkloadManager manages sandboxes across namespaces. Cross-namespace sandbox lifecycle management requires cluster-wide permissions. |\n447: \n448: ### Least Privilege Principles\n449: \n450: | Resource | Verbs | Reason |\n451: |----------|-------|--------|\n452: | pods | get, list, watch | Read-only monitoring; WorkloadManager creates pods via Sandbox CRD, not directly |\n453: | agentruntimes | get, list, watch | Read-only reference; WorkloadManager references AgentRuntimes but does not manage lifecycle |\n454: | agentruntimes/status | update, patch | Status updates only; no delete permission |\n455: | sandboxwarmpools/status | get, update, patch | Status subresource pattern; separate from main resource CRUD |\n456: | codeinterpreters/finalizers | update | Finalizer management only; limited to finalizer operations |\n457: | tokenreviews | create | One-shot authentication; no read/delete (ephemeral operation) |\n458: \n459: ---\n460: \n461: ## Implementation Timeline\n462: \n463: | Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n464: |-------|-------|--------|------------|\n465: | Phase 1: Router RBAC Foundation | T1.1-T1.5 | Completed | 100% |\n466: | Phase 2: WorkloadManager RBAC | T2.1-T2.7 | Completed | 100% |\n467: | Phase 3: Deployment Integration | T3.1-T3.3 | Completed | 100% |\n468: | Phase 4: Permission Validation | T4.1-T4.5 | Pending | 0% |\n469: | Phase 5: Helm Validation | T5.1-T5.5 | Pending | 0% |\n470: | Phase 6: Kubernetes API Validation | T6.1-T6.3 | Pending | 0% |\n471: | Phase 7: Permission Matrix Tests | T7.1-T7.8 | Pending | 0% |\n472: | Phase 8: Security Audit | T8.1-T8.5 | Pending | 0% |\n473: \n474: **Total Progress: 30% Complete (15/50 tasks)**\n475: \n476: ---\n477: \n478: ## References\n479: \n480: - Design: `changes/AR-031/design.md`\n481: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md`\n482: - Proposal: `changes/AR-031/proposal.md`\n483: - AR-030 Helm Chart Design: `changes/AR-030/design.md` (RBAC template patterns)\n484: - Kubernetes RBAC Documentation: https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/access-authn-authz/rbac/\n485: - Kubernetes API Reference: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n486: - Helm Template Functions: https://helm.sh/docs/chart_template_guide/function_list/\n487: - agent-sandbox CRDs: https://sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox\n\n(End of file - total 487 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-031 — RBAC 配置 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-031 — RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) |\n| Module | `manifests` |\n| Language | YAML |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Router RBAC Foundation (ST-1)\n\n- [ ] **T1.1**: Create Router ServiceAccount template with conditional rendering\n  - Purpose: Define ServiceAccount when `router.rbac.create=true`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-031/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775890174798,"end":1775890174835}}}}
